  "time_ut": 1661883003,
  "original_lang": "si",
  "original_title": "\u0d87\u0db8\u0dd9\u0dbb\u0dd2\u0d9a\u0dcf\u0db1\u0dd4 \u0db6\u0dd4\u0d82\u0dc0\u0dad\u0dca \u0db1\u0dd3\u0dad\u0dd2\u0dba\u0da7 \u0dc3\u0db8\u0dcf\u0db1 \u0db4\u0dca\u200d\u0dbb\u0dad\u0dd2\u0db4\u0dcf\u0daf\u0db1 \u0db8\u0dd9\u0dbb\u0da7\u0da7\u0dad\u0dca",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Provisions similar to the American Bungwat law in this country as well",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "President Ranil Wickramasinghe says that provisions similar to Chapter 11 of the American Civil Code are being introduced to Sri Lanka.",
        "Presenting the 2022 Amended Appropriation Bill (Budget Speech) to Parliament, he said this as the Minister of Finance.",
        "The President said that businesses affected by indebtedness should be reorganized, and the provisions on how to do so are stated in Chapter 11 of the Bankruptcy Code of the United States of America.",
        "He mentioned that simply being insolvent is not a reason to close down businesses, and that there is a method to reorganize businesses by restructuring assets and liabilities and getting rid of debt while running the business.",
        "The President suggested that similar new laws should be enforced in Sri Lanka."
      ],
